commit message:
Initial commit

Initial state is a few steps on from version 1.11.

Change network port number

Versions 1.11 and earlier have no method for detecting which versions
are being run in networked games. These versions will have too many
differences to later versions for them to be compatible.

This prevents earlier versions from networking with newer versions.

Add initialise shell script

The script initialises the android project so it can be compiled.
Add shell script header to build script

Add the armeabi cpu architecture

Doesn't increase file size very much at all.
Don't know to what extent armeabi devices can handle this game,
but might as well have the option.
Other architectures are probably much less important at this stage.
Makes a blank map default when none provided
Change version code to match version
Change Black Circles map name to Circles

Fix state being drawn and destroyed at the same time

On slow phones it is very likely for the state to take too long
to be destroyed and for the graphics thread to try to draw the
state object in the middle of the destroy process.
This is fixed by making the global state pointer NULL before
calling delete on the state object, thereby allowing the graphics
thread to see that there is no valid state object.

Replace smudge map with mandelbrot map

Smudge map image is far too big for the size of the app (570KB
compared to the average 20KB).
Fix bug, initialise.sh failing on first run

Merge pull request #8 from valerio-bozzolan/master-os

Localization support Italian language
